descriptions.value: Welcome home to this lovingly cared for, updated home in the Davis Spring community. Ideally located off Parmer, near the Apple campus and Austin's Tech Corridor and only 10 miles from Austin's 2nd downtown, The Domain where you can enjoy shopping, dining and entertainment! Upon entering, you'll be greeted by elegant new wood flooring, large windows framing your private back yard, a striking designer stone fireplace, and fresh paint throughout including a modern look to the stair banister. The bright kitchen features granite countertops, recently painted white cabinets, and state-of-the-art stainless steel appliances. Seamlessly connected to a charming breakfast area and welcoming living space, this open-concept design ensures effortless entertaining and family gatherings. The versatile first floor offers a spacious family room, an office or flex space, and a formal dining room. The second level showcases four generously proportioned bedrooms and a sizable loft, providing an ideal sanctuary after a busy day. The expansive backyard serves as a private retreat, boasting an impressive (newer) deck and magnificent trees. Enjoy captivating views of the lush landscape from numerous vantage points within the home. The Davis Spring community offers a wealth of amenities to complement your active lifestyle, including a 25-meter Junior Olympic pool, baby pool with splash pad, basketball court, tennis court, and 5 acres of verdant open space. descriptions.value: THE LIST PRICE REPRESENTS THE OPENING OFFER AMOUNT NET TO SELLER. AGENTS - PLEASE VIEW AGENT REMARKS IN BRIGHT MLS.Welcome to the well maintained 6504 Hopeton Avenue! Brick, semi-detached in the desirable Fallstaff area of Northwest Baltimore this 3-bedroom, 2.5 bathroom is located within walking distance to the mall, restaurants and retail stores. For your commute, you have access to I-695 and I-83. 6504 Hopeton Ave. has a stone front and back porch. The spacious living room and dining room has very low maintenance vinyl flooring with long lasting durability. There are ceiling fans throughout the house and plenty of natural lighting. The kitchen has granite gallery black countertops, a spacious island and stainless-steel appliances. The second floor has three spacious bedrooms with wall-to-wall carpet. There is also an attic with steps in the hallway area that has lots of storage. The fully finished basement is ideal for a family room, gym or office and has a full bathroom. There’s a separate area that houses your front-loading washer and dryer. The fenced in backyard is an awesome place for grilling and family time. There is also plenty of storage space in the shed. This property is move-in ready for a first-time homebuyer or investor looking to build a portfolio in an amazing neighborhood.Offers will be accepted through Tuesday, November 19, 2024, at 1:00 pm.AT SELLER'S DISCRETION, AN OFFER MAY BE ACCEPTED AT ANY TIME.

Plenty of parking with the extra side driveway along with the main driveway. Buy this charming "Home on the Hill" with confidence as the seller is including an all inclusive one year home warranty. Professional photos coming 11/6.

Gorgeous hardwood floors grace the main and upper levels. The large primary bedroom addition provides a serene and inviting retreat that overlooks the meticulously landscaped backyard. The three full bathrooms are renovated and beautiful. Skylights and updated windows make this home bright and inviting. The updated kitchen features an open and functional layout with convenient access to the back deck. The backyard is truly stunning and offers a large deck, beautiful stone hardscapes, and mature landscaping…. .it will be spectacular when the flowers begin to bloom! Caring for your lawn will be a breeze with the built-in underground sprinkler system in both the front and back yards. With plenty of open space to entertain friends and family, this entire property will be the envy of all.

descriptions.value: Welcome to this sensational townhome located in the 'Renewbold' development and offers just under 2k square feet! Presented with a lovely new exterior paint job, each home provides a reserved parking space. Built as New construction in 2015 and originally inspired to meet LEED Platinum environmental standards for household efficiencies, features include triple-pane, thick-foam insulation windows throughout the house, rain barrel in backyard garden that recycles water into the planter box, permeable pavers in the driveway/courtyard and Rooftop Deck with panoramic views of the Philadelphia Skyline. The home is custom fitted with Bosch Dishwasher, Bosch Oven, Kitchen Aide Refrigerator w/ Ice Maker and Water Filtration system, Ceiling fans in each room and custom fitted Window Blinds. Enter into home through the open concept kitchen/living space with 10ft ceilings and hardwood floors. Straight through the living room is a modern kitchen with tile backsplash, built in Bosch wall oven and a Bosch induction stovetop. Off of the kitchen is a finished basement offering a secondary living space, office, bedroom or even continued storage space. It is a very well lite area and even has another large closet space for storage. The basement closet also features a utility sink and Sub Zero commercial refrigerator for secondary cold space, all to be included it the sale of home. Circling back, the kitchen leads to the shared backdoor courtyard/driveway, with plenty of room provided for grilling and parking. Heading upstairs, the second and third floors have 9ft ceilings and hardwood floors throughout. On the second floor there are two bedrooms, as well as, a full bathroom and large laundry closet outfitted with a stackable Bosch washer/dryer. The third floor acts as the primary suite of the home with a large bedroom, en-suite bathroom, walk-in closet and even a bonus space with potential for many functions. Currently used as a remote office, the bonus space is also perfect for a seating area or can be outfitted with Wet Bar for entertaining guests on the rooftop deck. This area has sliding glass doors to a balcony space adjacent to a spiral staircase which teleports you to the Green Roof deck with panoramic views of the City Skyline. This home has so much to offer and is walking distance to bars and restaurants along the ever popular East Passyunk dining and shopping scene. Public transportation encompasses a bus route into Center City and the Broad Street Line subway station just a short walk out of the front door. Come check out this listing ASAP it won't remain long!

Sensational South Philly LEED Platinum 3BR, 2ba home with private, off-street PARKING in cool Newbold neighborhood. Part of the "re-Newbold" development, this home has the highest level of design as well as the best GREEN building features including: triple glazed windows, whole house ER ventilation, Energy Star rated appliances & HVAC, rain barrel & raised garden bed, super-insulated building envelope and a sedum green roof. Sustainability meets incredible design and ultra low energy costs - this home is smart as well as beautiful! Enter the open plan main level with 10' high ceilings, recessed lighting, ceiling fans and oak hardwood floors throughout. Sleek, state of the art kitchen has loads of cabinetry with soft close doors & drawers, stainless Bosch appliance suite, gorgeous Quartzite counters and classic subway tiled backsplash. The Island offers a great place for guests to share a glass of wine with the chef. Dramatic staircase ascends to the second level with two bedrooms (one used as an open den), stacked laundry station and a tiled hall bath with double vanity and tub/shower combination. Third floor is your gracious master suite. Bedroom has glass wall overlooking the main stair, ensuite lux tiled bath offers a glass enclosed shower and separate water closet. There is also a bonus space which makes a great study or solarium with sliding glass door to the terrace. Top of the house offers panoramic views of the city in every direction from your living GREEN ROOF deck - amazing place to entertain, garden or just chill. descriptions.value: A rare opportunity in Nonquitt—this newer-construction, turnkey 4-bedroom, 2.5-bath home sits in the heart of this historic seaside enclave, overlooking the 1st fairway of the community’s 9-hole golf course. Built in 2013, the home offers a fresh, like-new feel with a first-floor primary suite, a crisp white kitchen, laundry room, powder room, and a screened porch perfect for summer evenings. Upstairs, you’ll find a full bath, a den, and three generously sized bedrooms, each with access to a private balcony with fairway views. Thoughtfully landscaped for privacy, the property is framed by mature plantings and features an outdoor shower and full unfinished basement- a blank slate with finishing potential. As a Nonquitt proprietor, enjoy access to three sandy beaches, golf with no tee times, pickleball, tennis, a vibrant calendar of social events, and a beloved children’s day camp. No escalation clauses.

descriptions.value: Welcome to the Kendall II—a beautifully designed home featuring soaring two-story ceilings in both the foyer and great room, creating a dramatic and inviting first impression. Durable and stylish RevWood flooring flows throughout all main-level common areas, leading into a chef-inspired kitchen complete with shaker-style cabinetry, built-in stainless steel appliances, a custom tile backsplash, and elegant quartz countertops. The expansive eat-in island seamlessly connects to the great room, where a striking floor-to-ceiling tiled fireplace becomes the focal point of the space. The private primary suite offers a spa-like retreat with a garden tub, walk-in shower, and an oversized walk-in closet. A secondary bedroom and full bath are thoughtfully positioned near the front of the home, separated by a full-sized study—ideal for remote work or quiet focus. Upstairs, the spacious game room overlooks the great room below and flows into a dedicated media room pre-wired for surround sound. Bedroom three features its own en-suite bath and walk-in closet, while bedroom four enjoys a private bath just outside its door. Enjoy outdoor living on the extended Texas-sized covered patio that opens to a generously sized backyard—perfect for entertaining or relaxing in privacy. Additional storage is available with the optional 5' garage extension. Come see why so many are choosing to call Sauls Ranch East home—schedule your tour today!

descriptions.value: Under contract-accepting backup offers. Welcome to a true hidden gem—where luxury living meets hobbyist heaven! Set on 2.40 manicured acres, this stunning 3-bedroom, 3-bathroom home offers a rare combination of refined interiors, resort-style outdoor living, and exceptional space for collectors, car enthusiasts, and anyone who appreciates pristine land and craftsmanship. With 3,142 sq. ft. of living space, a dedicated theater room, and garage parking for five vehicles—including a two-car attached garage and a sprawling three-car detached garage—this property is built for those who want it all. The moment you arrive, the long winding drive, immaculate landscaping, and gated dog run welcome you into a property that feels like a private estate. Inside, warm finishes and thoughtful upgrades include a cozy fireplace, built-in bar with wine chiller, under-stair storage, and a recently remodeled guest bath with modern, elegant finishes. Entertain like never before in the screen-enclosed pool area, complete with a kickplate for pet safety, outdoor egg and gas stove, and lush garden views that invite tranquility and comfort. The oversized primary suite is a true retreat, boasting dual vanities, generous space, and views of the serene grounds. The home has been upgraded for both comfort and efficiency, with two brand new HVAC systems, a new well pump, new hot water heater, Pro Elite water filter, reverse osmosis, and additional attic insulation. All new windows let in natural light, while a whole-house security system with a dedicated security room ensures peace of mind. The home is also plumbed for a generator, ideal for those who want to be fully self-sufficient. Car collectors and hobbyists will fall in love with the expansive detached garage, perfect for vehicle storage, restoration projects, or converting into the ultimate workshop or studio. The beautiful outdoor space includes water lines to the garden for easy maintenance, creating a true balance of beauty and functionality. Whether you’re chasing the perfect property to support your passions, or simply looking for a peaceful and private place to call home—this one-of-a-kind estate checks every box.

descriptions.value: 529 N High St is a single family residence located in Martinsburg, WV 25404. Built in 1900, this property features 4 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, 13,504 sq ft lot, and 1,724 sq ft of living space. This property recently sold for $148,000 on 03/03/2020.

Welcome to this charming 3 bed, 2,5 bath single-family home that seamlessly blends comfort and functionality. This completely remoldeled residence boasts a metal roof, new HVAC system, new updated electrical, and new appliances to ensuring worry-free living for years to come. As you step inside, you'll be greeted by a warm, freshly painted, comforting and inviting atmosphere with an abundance of natural light. Main level features an open floor plan with new LVP flooring, dining area, original exposed brick, beautiful staircase, and half bath. The open floor plan enhances the sense of space, creating an ideal setting for both everyday living and entertaining guests. The heart of the home features a modern kitchen equipped with top-of-the-line appliances, new cabinets, granite countertops, walk in pantry and offers a perfect space for culinary enthusiasts. Upstairs has 3 beds, 2 full baths and washer/dryer with new LVP flooring/carpet. The highlight of this property is the detached in-law suite, providing versatility and privacy for extended family or guests. You could even use this as a rental unit for extra income. There is a living area/bedroom, and bathroom with washer/dryer. This additional space is perfect for multigenerational living or as a private retreat. The exterior of the home is equally impressive, featuring a big fenced in yard, huge side yard, detached garage with plenty of space, off street parking and landscaping that create a picturesque curb appeal. Conveniently located near hospitals, doctors offices, schools, parks, shopping, 81 and much more, this home offers easy access to so much. The combination of modern upgrades, thoughtful design, and the detached in-law suite make this property a rare find in today's market. Don't miss the opportunity to make this house your new home. Schedule a showing today and experience the lifestyle that awaits you! Schedule a Private Showing

See it today!

This residential 2.21-acre property for sale in Montgomery County, MD can be your dream property with a 7,512 square foot house. View this Brookeville property today.

Welcome to Howard Hall, a stately historical manor home dating to 1737. Ideally situated upon a knoll on 2.5 of the most private acres, it has been home to some of Montgomery County's founding families. It was modernized in the 1930s and those original features still define the home; 1' thick American black walnut wide plank flooring, wood moldings, bohemian crystal chandeliers, a stained glass wall, expansive terraces in sparkling West Virginia fieldstone, tall 10' ceilings and large windows that make it light and bright. The most enchanting feature of the home is its magnificent curved staircase which leads you past the 4' chandelier. Then, prepare to be wowed as you enter the magazine-worthy 2019 kitchen done at a cost of well over 150k. From the handmade tile on the heated floor, custom cabinetry with inset doors to the stunning natural quartzite slab counters, unlacquered Barber Wilsons London brass fixtures, to boxed beam ceilings, every effort was made to evoke the feeling of a period kitchen. The 'piece de resistance' of the kitchen is without a doubt the pale blue 'La Cornue' range. Outside, the grounds inspire with their mature trees and winding paths and hedging that provides so much privacy that many neighbors don't even know the home is there! Two ancient Linden trees anchor the front yard and one of them is a Montgomery County champion tree. Just 6 minutes from the ICC/MD200 highway, and a pleasant 7-minute walk through the park gets you to the town of Olney with its many fine restaurants. Some mentionables include a fruit tree orchard, dog kennel or chicken coop, basement workshop, finished attic with five storage walk-in closets, dedicated laundry and housekeeping space, formal entrance and drive, back entrance and drive, neighborhood pool membership available, no historical restrictions and the property sides to a greenbelt. Freshly painted with Farrow and Ball throughout. If you are finding large homes cavernous and new homes already looking dated, Howard Hall is the perfect blend of a cozy and classic livable family home. Please note that the formal entrance is found at 18900 Alpenglow Lane where the lockbox is located.

It was modernized in the 1930s and those original features still define the home; 1' thick American black walnut wide plank flooring, wood moldings, bohemian crystal chandeliers, a stained glass wall, expansive terraces in sparkling West Virginia fieldstone, tall 10' ceilings and large windows that make it light and bright. The most enchanting feature of the home is its magnificent curved staircase which leads you past the 4' chandelier. Then, prepare to be wowed as you enter the magazine-worthy 2019 kitchen done at a cost of well over 150k. From the handmade tile on the heated floor, custom cabinetry with inset doors to the stunning natural quartzite slab counters, unlacquered Barber Wilsons London brass fixtures, to boxed beam ceilings, every effort was made to evoke the feeling of a period kitchen. The 'piece de resistance' of the kitchen is without a doubt the pale blue 'La Cornue' range. Outside, the grounds inspire with their mature trees and winding paths and hedging that provides so much privacy that many neighbors don't even know the home is there! Two ancient Linden trees anchor the front yard and one of them is a Montgomery County champion tree. * * Main gate entrance is 18900 ALPENGLOW not Gold Mine Place * * Welcome to Howard Hall originally built in the 1700's, reconstructed in the 1930's with major renovations in the 1970's. In 2019 the kitchen was rebuilt featuring handmade tiles on the heated floors, custom cabinetry with inset doors, natural quartzite slab counters, unlacquered Barber Wilsons London brass fixtures, boxed beam ceilings and a blue 'La Cornue' six burner range with double oven and a pot filler on the back splash. Many gourmet features for your entertaining needs. In addition, off the kitchen is a pantry, spacious mud room and back staircase for convenience in family living. The FirstFloor laundry room is spacious enough for a second refrigerator, freezer, built ins and has lots of light from the large window. A "picture is worth a thousand words" and the attached photos and floor plan sketch depict all the historic features. The large windows, 10' ceilings, an 8' X 10' stained glass window containing several family crests and coat of arms, all within view of the spectacular curved staircase featuring solid black walnut railing. The marble entrance foyer with a Bohemian crystal chandelier leads to random width pegged black walnut flooring. Enjoy entertaining in the Summer Room with multiple archways and French doors leading to another terrace and garden. The ample beautiful lawns surrounding the house are maintained effortlessly with two robotic lawn mowers. The back gate entrance off of Gold Mine Place has a hidden chicken coop/dog kennel and leads to ample parking plus a three car garage. Upon entering the main gate on Alpenglow to the right there is a maintenance free wildflower garden to enjoy all summer through most of the Fall. Approaching on the left is ample parking for all your quests. The spacious front yard holds the 200 year old awarding winning Linden Tree. Multiple terraces and three awnings with remotes aid in enjoying the breathtaking views all summer long. The entire 2.2-acre lot is fenced with two entrance gates. Viewing this home in person will be memorable!
